  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of disguising the origin of illegally obtained money, typically by means of transfers involving foreign banks or legitimate businesses. Specific legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but typically involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the \"cleaned\" money into the legitimate economy\n\nThe precise legal definition depends on the specific jurisdiction and its anti-money laundering (AML) laws.",
